 exploration of their religious ideas. Contributors to the volume depict a variety of local areas where this lineage is prominent and highlight how the Nāths have been a link between religious, metaphysical, and even medical traditions in India.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aNātha sect. 0aYoga. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Hindu Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Yoga. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / General.2bisacsh1 aAgrawal, Purushottam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanerjee-Dube, Ishita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGold, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGordon White, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrodzins Gold, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiss, Csaba, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorenzen, David N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLorenzen, David N., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMuñoz, Adrián, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuñoz, Adrián, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOndračka, Lubomír, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438438924423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438438924/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles